President Donald J. Trump received a briefing on Hurricane Dorian from several officials, including the Acting Administrator of FEMA, the Acting Assistant Secretary of Commerce for Environmental Observation and Prediction, and the Homeland Security and Counterterrorism Advisor. The President was updated on the preparation efforts for the storm and discussed its projected track and potential impacts. He expressed his support for those in the storm's path and emphasized the importance of providing assistance and heeding the warnings of state and local officials.